tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a comprehensive aesthetic overhaul.
  The generic design was replaced with a calming, sleep-themed palette, and
  various UI components and sections were refined for a more professional and
  engaging user experience.
overview: The user wanted to improve the aesthetics of their sleep questionnaire
  app, which they felt was too generic. I started by reviewing the app's
  existing styling across global CSS, layout, and various UI and section
  components. I identified several areas for improvement, including the color
  palette, backgrounds, form sections, and overall visual personality. I then
  implemented a new sleep-themed color palette with deep indigos, purples, and
  teals. The main questionnaire form was updated with decorative background
  elements, a redesigned progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on the
  card header. The intro section was transformed with a hero element and feature
  cards, and form components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders
  received a more polished look. Finally, the report section was updated with
  consistent gradient headers and improved content styling. The changes were
  verified through linter checks and visual inspection in the browser, resulting
  in a calming, professional, and engaging user interface.
